66 (3) 'Internal response team' means the team of school personnel established pursuant to
67 paragraph (7) (6) of subsection (c) of this Code section responsible for oversight of an
68 emergency response to a person in cardiac arrest and implementation of the emergency
69 action plan.
70 (4) 'School' means a public school in this state which provides K-12 education.
71 (b) No later than July 1, 2025, each school in this state shall have at least one functional
72 automated external defibrillator on site at such school at all times and easily accessible
73 during all school hours and during any school related function, including athletic practices,
74 athletic competitions, and other occasions where students and others will be present, for
75 use during emergencies.
76 (c) Each school shall:
77 (1) Ensure that each member of the internal response team and any other expected users
78 of the automated external defibrillator receive American Heart Association or American
79 Red Cross training in cardiopulmonary resuscitation and automated external defibrillator
80 use or complete an equivalent nationally recognized course;
81 (2) Notify the appropriate emergency medical services system of the existence and
82 location of each automated external defibrillator prior to said automated external
83 defibrillator being placed in use;
84 (3) Ensure that the automated external defibrillator is maintained and tested according
85 to the manufacturer's operational guidelines;
86 (4) Ensure that there is involvement of a licensed physician or other person authorized
87 by the Georgia Composite Medical Board in the site's automated external defibrillator
88 program to ensure compliance with requirements for training, notification, and
89 maintenance;
90 (5)(4) Establish a written emergency action plan that adheres to nationally recognized
91 standards and that establishes specific steps to take during a cardiac emergency in a
92 school setting. Such plan shall be designed to provide for an effective system for
