93 communication between members of the internal response team and other school
94 officials, ensuring that the internal response team or other designated personnel activate
95 the emergency medical services system as soon as reasonably possible after any person
96 renders emergency care or treatment to a person in cardiac arrest by using an automated
97 external defibrillator and report any clinical use of the automated external defibrillator
98 to the licensed physician or other person authorized by the Georgia Composite Medical
99 Board who is supervising the program, and ensuring that emergency medical services
100 personnel are led directly to the exact location of the person in cardiac arrest;
101 (6)(5) Beginning in the 2025-2026 school year and each school year thereafter, conduct
102 a minimum of two emergency action plan practice drills per school year, with at least one
103 per semester. One such practice drill may be a tabletop drill to walk through a
104 hypothetical scenario and the courses of action a school will need to take before, during,
105 and after a cardiac emergency. The emergency action plan practice drills shall include
106 various locations on school grounds and responses to different hypothetical situations;
107 (7)(6) Establish a designated internal response team composed of:
108 (A) At least five school staff members;
109 (B) One or more designated team leads trained in cardiopulmonary resuscitation and
110 automated external defibrillator use and responsible for oversight of an emergency
111 response;
112 (C) One or more designated cardiopulmonary resuscitation leads trained in
113 cardiopulmonary resuscitation and automated external defibrillator use;
114 (D) One or more designated automated external defibrillator leads, responsible for
115 knowing the location of automated external defibrillators, retrieving automated external
116 defibrillators, and maintenance of automated external defibrillators; and
117 (E) One or more designated communication leads responsible for activating the
118 emergency medical services system, facilitating directions to the person in cardiac
