119 arrest for emergency medical services personnel upon arrival at the school, and
120 coordinating communications with the designated team lead or leads; and
121 (8)(7) Apprise all school personnel of the location of automated external defibrillators
122 and the members of the internal response team.
123 (d) Subject to appropriations by the General Assembly, the Department of Education shall
124 provide funds to local school systems to assist in the purchase of automated external
