129 SECTION 4.
130 Said chapter is further amended by revising Code Section 20-2-851, relating to use of
131 accumulated sick leave for personal or professional reasons, as follows:
132 "20-2-851.
133 During any school year, personnel may utilize up to a maximum of three five days of any
134 accumulated sick leave for the purpose of absenting themselves from their duties for
135 personal or professional reasons if prior approval of their absence is given by the local
136 school superintendent or his or her authorized representative; provided, however, that the
137 absence is not in conflict with a local board of education policy concerning school days on
138 which the presence of the personnel requesting absence is essential for effective school
139 operation. No grant of approval for an absence permitted under this Code section shall be
140 conditioned upon disclosure of the specific purpose for which such absence is sought, nor
141 shall any such grant of approval be withheld or denied because of the failure or refusal of
142 personnel to disclose the specific purpose for which such an absence is sought; provided,
143 however, that personnel may be requested to state whether the absence is sought under the
144 category of 'personal' or 'professional' absence."
